---
import BgGrid from "@/components/assets/BgGrid.astro";
---

<section class="border-white/10 border-b divide-y divide-white/10 bg-[#0a0a0a]">
  <div class="p-8 md:p-16 relative">
    <BgGrid />
    <p
      class="text-white font-bold uppercase tracking-tighter lg:text-6xl text-2xl relative leading-none"
    >
      Security is not about the absence of risk, but the <span class="text-[#ff5f1f]">resilience to survive it.</span>
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-8 md:p-16">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
      <p class="text-white/60 font-medium uppercase lg:text-xl text-lg leading-tight">
        I reject the idea that security must hinder usability. True infrastructure security should be <span class="text-white">transparent</span>—protecting the user without obstructing the workflow.
      </p>
      <p class="text-white/60 font-medium uppercase lg:text-xl text-lg leading-tight">
        Investing in security is not a diversion of resources; it is a <span class="text-white">preservation of value.</span> Robust defense ensures that innovation isn't erased by a single point of failure.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>